NA 中的血液癌症保护性遗传变异&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/genetic-variation-reveals-a-homeotic-long-noncoding-rna-that-modulates-human-hematopoietic-stem-cells.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 12:36:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/genetic-variation-reveals-a-homeotic-long-noncoding-rna-that-modulates-human-hematopoietic-stem-cells</guid></item><item><title>人类 DNA-PKcs 促进 NHEJ 期间断裂的 DNA 末端结构独立性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-dna-pkcs-promotes-broken-dna-end-structure-independence-during-nhej</link><description>DNA-PKcs 是否是非同源末端连接所必需的，在生化方面尚不清楚。通过优化反应条件，Fujii 和 Modesti 表明 DNA-PKcs 发挥着建设性作用，导致粘端 DNA 底物和平端 DNA 底物之间的修复效率无法区分。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/human-dna-pkcs-promotes-broken-dna-end-structure-independence-during-nhej2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 12:21:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/human-dna-pkcs-promotes-broken-dna-end-structure-independence-during-nhej</guid></item><item><title>摘要：代谢综合征和过量饮酒导致肝损伤和纤维化，其特征是肝星状细胞胶原沉积增加</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/abstract-metabolic-syndrome-and-excessive-alcohol-consumption-lead-to-liver-injury-and-fibrosis-characterized-by-increased-collagen-deposition-from-hepatic-stellate-cells</link><description>https://doi.org/10.1172/JCI197923&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/abstract137.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 12:06:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/abstract-metabolic-syndrome-and-excessive-alcohol-consumption-lead-to-liver-injury-and-fibrosis-characterized-by-increased-collagen-deposition-from-hepatic-stellate-cells</guid></item><item><title>章鱼大脑的工作方式和人类一样吗？或者还有其他变得聪明的方法吗？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/do-octopus-brains-work-like-humans-or-is-there-another-way-to-be-smart</link><description>就像脊椎动物一样，头足类动物（例如章鱼和鱿鱼）也拥有复杂的大脑。神经科学家纷纷向它们寻求关于智力如何进化的见解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/do-octopus-brains-work-like-humans-or-is-there-another-way-to-be-smart.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 11:51:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/do-octopus-brains-work-like-humans-or-is-there-another-way-to-be-smart</guid></item><item><title>实验推进了利用移植神经元恢复视力的努力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/experiments-advance-efforts-to-restore-vision-with-transplanted-neurons</link><description>约翰霍普金斯大学医学院的研究人员表示，他们已经成功证明，破坏长期以来被怀疑阻碍移植神经细胞生长和存活的眼睛结构可能有助于恢复视神经损伤患者的视力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/experiments-advance-efforts-to-restore-vision-with-transplanted-neurons2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 11:36:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/experiments-advance-efforts-to-restore-vision-with-transplanted-neurons</guid></item><item><title>对 800 名被监禁男子的脑部扫描发现精神病与皮质表面积扩大有关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-scans-of-800-incarcerated-men-link-psychopathy-to-an-expanded-cortical-surface-area</link><description>一项针对 800 多名被监禁男子的大规模脑成像研究表明，高度精神病态的人拥有扩大的皮层表面积和压缩的大脑物理组织，为同理心和反社会行为的生物学提供了新的线索。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-scans-of-800-incarcerated-men-link-psychopathy-to-an-expanded-cortical-surface-area.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 11:21:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-scans-of-800-incarcerated-men-link-psychopathy-to-an-expanded-cortical-surface-area</guid></item><item><title>步态障碍的神经调节</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/neuromodulation-for-gait-disorders</link><description>僵直、虚弱和不平衡等步态障碍仍然对神经系统疾病的标准疗法有抵抗力。这篇综述探讨了神经调节方面的进展，从完善深部脑刺激到整合脊髓和分布式策略。它讨论了自适应神经技术、机制见解以及用于定制时空精确干预措施以恢复步态控制的框架。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neuromodulation-for-gait-disorders.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Mon, 04 May 2026 11:06:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/neuromodulation-for-gait-disorders</guid></item></channel></rss>